{
  "texts": [
    "The unpooling branch cleverly restores the pooled graph to its original resolution, ensuring that the representations of entity mentions can be accurately extracted, providing a new perspective on long text processing.",
    "In addition, in the field of text representation learning, (Gao et al. 2019) incorporates graph neural network and graph pooling techniques to propose a graph-based text representation method.",
    "Through the text-to-graph conversion, the learning of graph neural networks and the use of graph pooling, the method is able to capture the structural and semantic information in the text in depth and generate rich and effective text representations, which lays a solid foundation for subsequent tasks such as text classification and information retrieval.",
    "In the field of computer vision, graph pooling methods have been widely used for tasks such as semantic segmentation, image classification, 3D point cloud segmentation, and pose estimation due to their ability to handle complex data structures.",
    "For these tasks, researchers have proposed a variety of innovative graph pooling strategies that significantly improve the performance of the model."
  ]
}